attributionInfo.brokerName: Missouri Home, Farm & Land Realty, LLC

data.description: Beautiful 20 acres, 12 wooded acres and 8 open. Home is up on the top of the property with beautiful views from the back yard. New 30x48 steel building that has concrete floors, windows, 3 sets of doors and plumbed for a half bath in one corner. We have a chicken coop that has 2 areas inside, one is used for chickens with roosts and nesting boxes. We used the front for storage and our ducks. A cabin is also on the property with a living area, galley kitchen, handicap accessible bathroom with a walk in shower and a bedroom space in the back. It has a ramp on one side and cute porch on the front with views of the back yard. There is an additional septic installed for that cabin and is inline to the steel building for that bathroom.  40 ft shipping container for storage, firepit, garden area, circle drive, two ponds, fruit trees, perennial flowers around the yard.  The house has three bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, a sun porch, laundry area and vaulted ceilings in one part of the house. Living room just got hardwood floors. Two bedrooms just got new carpet. Living room is bright and sunny and we put in a big wood burning fireplace.  Newer stainless-steel refrigerator and dishwasher, the stove is electric convection. Gas dryer and washer included. The roof is ready to be redone, it will have a brand new white metal roof once finished . Newer heat pump offers heat and cooling. Big walk-in closets in two bedrooms.  This property is just so peaceful. You cannot see any neighbors from the house but they are all so nice. Anytime we have needed anything they are the first to jump and help us. We need to downsize, or we really would not sell. We love it here. Come put your personal touches on this home and enjoy the beautiful property. There is pond down the hill that is spring fed and there is a creek that runs seasonal through the woods. There are some trails through the woods and it is fenced on 3 sides. High speed internet was just installed.
